A 25-year-old woman from Jabulani‚ Soweto‚ was allegedly found in a pool of blood at her boyfriend’s place over the weekend. The woman had visited her 42-year-old boyfriend’s home in Zola North on Sunday. Around 4pm a neighbour alerted the police to the scuffle that allegedly led to her death. Constable Phindile Mavuso‚ spokesperson for Jabulani police‚ said the suspect was found on the scene. “When police arrived they found the suspect with the body in a pool of blood. Her upper body had multiple stab wounds. A community member alerted the police and it was alleged that they had a fight‚” said Mavuso. A case of murder was opened. The suspect is appearing in the Protea Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday.